  Two people were burnt beyond recognition after three cars
crashed along the R81 road between Giyani and Mooketsi in Limpopo. It is alleged that two Isuzu bakkies were travelling from
Giyani to Mooketsi when they collided and one of the drivers allegedly lost
control of the vehicle and collided head on with a third oncoming car, a Ford
Ranger. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said during this
collision, all the three motor vehicles caught fire, one Isuzu bakkie, with two
occupants a male driver and a female passenger were burnt to death. Whereas, the other Isuzu bakkie with two occupants, a driver
and a passenger, survived without injuries and the Ford Ranger with three
occupants including the driver, sustained serious injuries . They were then taken to hospital for medical treatment. At this stage, the cause of this collision is not clear. Ngoepe said the process of identifying the two deceased
including the forensic tests are still underway. 